lattice3dshell_dmg_bend_n7.out
Shell-mode lattice3d, latticedamage, hybrid layered (N=7): pure out-of-plane bending. Tension-face cracking propagates through-thickness as theta_y is increased. Regression check on the layered damage path.
StaticStructural nsteps 100 rtolv 1.e-6 ddm 2 2 5 ddv 1 1.e-2 ddltf 2 nmodules 1
errorcheck
domain 3dLattice
OutputManager tstep_all dofman_all element_all
ndofman 2 nelem 1 ncrosssect 1 nmat 1 nbc 1 nic 0 nltf 2
node 1 coords 3 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 bc 6 1 1 1 1 1 1
node 2 coords 3 1.000000e-01 0.000000e+00 0.000000e+00 bc 6 1 1 0 1 0 1
lattice3D 1 nodes 2 1 2 crossSect 1 mat 1 shellnormal 3 0.0 0.0 1.0 polycoords 12 0.05 -0.05 -0.005   0.05 0.05 -0.005   0.05 0.05 0.005   0.05 -0.05 0.005
latticecs 1 material 1 nlayers 7
latticedamage 1 d 2400. talpha 0.0 e 30.e9 e0 1.e-4 wf 1.e-4 a1 0.5 a2 1.0
BoundaryCondition 1 loadTimeFunction 1 prescribedvalue 0.0
ConstantFunction 1 f(t) 1.
PiecewiseLinFunction 2 nPoints 2 t 2 0. 100. f(t) 2 0. 1.
#%BEGIN_CHECK% tolerance 1.e-2
## Element L=0.1 m, rectangular cross-section b=0.1, t=0.01, shellnormal +z.
## theta_y prescribed at node 2 (free w, all other dofs fixed) -> pure
## out-of-plane bending with no transverse shear (w solves to give gamma_xz=0).
## Hybrid layered N=7: layer IPs see eps_axial = z*kappa; outermost
## tension-face layer reaches e0 first and starts to damage at theta ~ 2 mrad.
## Step 10 (theta = 1.0 mrad): still elastic, M = E*I2*kappa = 2.5 N*m.
#REACTION tStep 10  number 1 dof 5 value -2.5000e+00
## Step 25 (theta = 2.5 mrad): tension-face layer past peak, softening begins.
#REACTION tStep 25  number 1 dof 5 value -6.1029e+00
## Step 50 (theta = 5.0 mrad): damage front migrating through the thickness.
#REACTION tStep 50  number 1 dof 5 value -9.5508e+00
## Step 100 (theta = 10.0 mrad): well into the softening branch.
#REACTION tStep 100 number 1 dof 5 value -1.5337e+01
#%END_CHECK%
